This grim and claustrophobic drama chronicles the lives of the prisoners in Colditz Castle from the arrival of the first British prisoners after Dunkirk until the liberation of the castle by the Americans in 1945. Colditz was a &quot;special&quot; camp, designed by the Nazis to hold high-risk and politically important prisoners. Many of the series' plots are based on real events.

